      {
        "id": 4096529,
        "name": "\u0104\u0146\u0257\u0157\u0119\u0175 \u0136\u013c\u03cb\u01e5",
        "username": "Andrew_K",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/andrew_k/{size}/279879_2.png",
        "created_at": "2023-06-18T18:27:08.163Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Headed to Piedmont and Tuscany in the Fall to celebrate our 20th anniversary. Going to a few restaurants with extremely deep cellars and imagine I will be able to find some 2003s on some of the wine lists. But given that it\u2019s a tough vintage pretty much everywhere, I expect it will be an exercise more in sentimentality than a great wine experience.</p>\n<p>Are there any Italian producers or cuv\u00e9es worth seeking out from 2003 if I can find them?</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 9,
        "updated_at": "2023-06-18T18:27:08.163Z",
        "reply_count": 0,
        "reply_to_post_number": null,
        "quote_count": 0,
        "incoming_link_count": 79,
        "reads": 133,
        "readers_count": 132,
